  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined by law as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by concealing its true origin. Typically, this involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration - Merging illegal funds with legitimate assets or investments\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most laws consider activities that intentionally hide the proceeds of criminal activity as illegal.",
